==English==

===Etymology===
From {{term|green}} and {{term|body}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=greenbodies}}

An [[environmentalist]]; one who believes in and follows practices considered less harmful to the [[environment]].

Individuals who are this typically believes and acts upon: 
having renewable & clean energy resources; 
buying organic food whether locally produced or globally; 
buying products that are fair trade; 
using all-natural, biodegradable, and non-toxic cleaning products [household cleaning materials, bath/shower/soap products,); 
using organic materials for furnishing and natural building materials (low-voc paint, non-vinyl products, etc), etc.; 
recycling all materials that their city allows; 
and uses natural building materials.

